    "content": "**CONFIRM** — context-dependent, both acceptable.\n\n\"Nothingness\" and \"the void\" do different phenomenological work. \"Nothingness\" is abstract and conceptual (the absence of being, Sartrean néant). \"The void\" is spatial and experiential (an encountered emptiness, something you stand before). The author's 虚无 operates in both registers depending on the passage — sometimes as a philosophical concept (\"nothingness is not produced or created\"), sometimes as something existentially confronted (\"the ruins left behind are called nihilism\"). Locking in a single default would flatten this range.\n\nThe NEVER-emptiness rule for 空/śūnyatā distinction is correct and essential."
